comment_data.body:
@justinmk 
Thanks!  (used in https://github.com/Shougo/deoplete.nvim/pull/212)

I guess it should be added to the doc with e.g. `strftime()`?!

@blueyed I actually added a way to get the current time with nanosecond precision in #5189 (not merged).

Specific lines: https://github.com/tweekmonster/neovim/blob/d15365479a8a1dc484247fb6dbe100128d3a0eb0/src/nvim/os/time.c#L123-L131

It could be used make a `localtimef()` Vim function.  I can't attest to whether or not it's truly the best way to get the fractional time, but it was accurate enough for my needs.  It probably needs the `init_time_*` variables reset once in a while so it'll be less affected by crossing time boundaries.
